Step 6 is the magic step! 
1- be sure to use high quality products. Cheap shampoo/conditioner/products will fill your hair with waxy, heavy, buildup that will not be good for you hair over time. Using @amika Vault line
2- make sure you bellow dry your roots at a 90° angle to get max lift. Using @babylissprousa 
3- use dry shampoo right after your blow dry. You could even use a play powder too! Using @designmehair dry shampoo
4- if your ends need to be tamed, use a lightweight oil on ends only. Using pomifera hair oil (link in bio)
5- when flat ironing your hair, don’t flat iron the roots. If you have curly hair, get the curls out during the blow dry. Do a light curl away from the face and fork a “c” on the rest of the ends. Using @chihaircare 
6- use the @voloom on the roots for max volume- this helps my hair stay voluminous for days! Code BLUSHBASICS20
7- light texture spray for hold! Using @kenraprofessional

Three things you might be doing to age your face. If you’re over 30, switch it up and keep your face looking youthful!
Mistakes:
